casebody.data:
Martha Hoare, administrator of Henry Hoare against Charles Muloy. Messrs. J. B. M'Kean and S. Levy, pro quer. Mr. Heatly, pro def.

Report of referees set aside, because they awarded that the plaintiff an administratrix, should give security for a book debt to the defendant.

Exceptions to the report of referees, who amongst other things,, had awarded that the plaintiff should give security for a book debt to the defendant.

For this cause, the court without difficulty, set aside the report. Submission to a reference is no admission of assets. 5 Term. Rep. 6.
